---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Installation - Hovue"
  description="Learn how to install Hovue in your Vue 3 or Nuxt 3 project."
  prev={{ url: '/docs', title: 'Introduction' }}
  next={{ url: '/docs/quick-start', title: 'Quick Start' }}
>
  <h1>Installation</h1>

  <p>
    Get started with Hovue in minutes. Choose the installation method that best fits your project.
  </p>

  <h2>Package Managers</h2>

  <p>Install Hovue using your preferred package manager:</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    <span style="color: var(--text-muted);"># npm</span><br />
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">npm</span>
    <span style="color: var(--orange);">install</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">hovue</span><br /><br />
    <span style="color: var(--text-muted);"># yarn</span><br />
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">yarn</span>
    <span style="color: var(--orange);">add</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">hovue</span><br /><br />
    <span style="color: var(--text-muted);"># pnpm</span><br />
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">pnpm</span>
    <span style="color: var(--orange);">add</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">hovue</span><br /><br />
    <span style="color: var(--text-muted);"># bun</span><br />
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">bun</span>
    <span style="color: var(--orange);">add</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">hovue</span>
  </div>

  <h2>Vue 3</h2>

  <p>For Vue 3 projects, import icons directly in your components:</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">import</span> &#123; <span style="color: var(--orange);"
      >HoArrowRight</span
    >, <span style="color: var(--orange);">HoCheck</span> &#125; <span style="color: var(--purple);"
      >from</span
    >
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">'hovue'</span><br /><br />
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">export default</span> &#123;<br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">components</span>: &#123;<br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>,<br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoCheck</span><br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&#125;<br />
    &#125;
  </div>

  <h2>Nuxt 3</h2>

  <p>For Nuxt 3 projects, use the Nuxt module for auto-imports:</p>

  <h3>1. Install the module</h3>

  <div class="docs-code">
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">npm</span>
    <span style="color: var(--orange);">install</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">hovue</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">@hovue/nuxt</span>
  </div>

  <h3>2. Add to nuxt.config.ts</h3>

  <div class="docs-code">
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">export default</span> defineNuxtConfig(&#123;<br />
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">modules</span>: [<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >'@hovue/nuxt'</span
    >]<br />
    &#125;)
  </div>

  <p>That's it! Icons are now auto-imported and ready to use in your templates.</p>

  <h2>Vite</h2>

  <p>Hovue works seamlessly with Vite. No additional configuration needed.</p>

  <div class="docs-note">
    <strong>Note:</strong> Hovue requires Vue 3.3+ and supports both Composition API and Options API.
  </div>

  <h2>TypeScript</h2>

  <p>TypeScript definitions are included. No additional setup required.</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">import</span>
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">type</span> &#123; <span style="color: var(--orange);"
      >IconProps</span
    > &#125; <span style="color: var(--purple);">from</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">'hovue'</span>
  </div>

  <h2>Tree Shaking</h2>

  <p>Hovue is fully tree-shakeable. Only import the icons you use:</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    <span style="color: var(--text-muted);">// ✅ Good - only imports what you need</span><br />
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">import</span> &#123; <span style="color: var(--orange);"
      >HoArrowRight</span
    > &#125; <span style="color: var(--purple);">from</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">'hovue'</span><br /><br />
    <span style="color: var(--text-muted);">// ❌ Bad - imports entire library</span><br />
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">import</span>
    <span style="color: var(--orange);">*</span>
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">as</span>
    <span style="color: var(--orange);">Hovue</span>
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">from</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">'hovue'</span>
  </div>

  <h2>Next Steps</h2>

  <p>
    Now that you've installed Hovue, check out the <a href="/docs/quick-start">Quick Start</a> guide to
    learn how to use icons in your project.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
